From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 15:11:05 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] drm/meson: realign DW MIPI DSI lane-byte counter on
 bootloader handoff
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When the bootloader hands off a running DSI host, the DW host's
internal lane-byte counter - the per-line state machine that lays the
24bpp R G B byte stream onto the MIPI lanes - comes up at a random
byte offset on each cold boot. With the mod-3 counter starting at 0,
1, or 2 the panel sees R G B / G B R / B R G respectively, and the
matching pixel-counter mis-alignment shows up as a horizontal shift
on a vertical-stripe test pattern.

In meson_dw_mipi_dsi_probe's bootloader-up branch, toggle DSI_PWR_UP
(write SHUTDOWNZ=0, brief delay, write SHUTDOWNZ=1). The host's state
machines reset without touching PHY_RSTZ; the PHY stays locked, the
encoder keeps clocking pixels, and on the next HSYNC the host re-emits
the long-packet header at lane-byte 0. The panel sees one frame of
disrupted output (a brief dim flicker on a still-lit backlight) and
the colour and offset are deterministic from then on.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_dw_mipi_dsi.c | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_dw_mipi_dsi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_dw_mipi_dsi.c
index 10b8f527b..3fe2e9880 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_dw_mipi_dsi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/meson/meson_dw_mipi_dsi.c
@@ -350,6 +350,29 @@ static int meson_dw_mipi_dsi_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		reset_control_assert(mipi_dsi->top_rst);
 		usleep_range(10, 20);
 		reset_control_deassert(mipi_dsi->top_rst);
+	} else {
+		/*
+		 * The DW DSI host's lane-byte counter - the per-line state
+		 * machine that lays the 24bpp R G B byte stream onto the
+		 * MIPI lanes - comes up at a random byte offset on each
+		 * cold boot when the bootloader leaves the host running.
+		 * With the mod-3 byte counter starting at 0, 1, or 2 the
+		 * panel sees R G B / G B R / B R G respectively, producing
+		 * a cyclic colour permutation; the matching pixel-counter
+		 * mis-alignment shows up as a horizontal shift on a
+		 * vertical-stripe pattern.
+		 *
+		 * Toggling DSI_PWR_UP (write SHUTDOWNZ=0, brief delay,
+		 * write SHUTDOWNZ=1) clears the host state machines without
+		 * touching PHY_RSTZ. The PHY stays locked, the encoder
+		 * keeps clocking pixels, and on the next HSYNC the host
+		 * re-emits the long-packet header at lane-byte 0. The
+		 * panel sees one frame of disrupted output, which on a
+		 * still-lit backlight reads as a brief dim flicker.
+		 */
+		writel_relaxed(0, mipi_dsi->base + 0x04);
+		usleep_range(10, 20);
+		writel_relaxed(1, mipi_dsi->base + 0x04);
 	}

 	/* MIPI DSI Controller */
--
